product_name: CliniqueHigh Impact High-Fi Full Volume Mascara
summary: SummaryHighlightsSustainable PackagingClinique's High Impact High-Fi Mascara is an ultra-pigmented, fiber-infused mascara that amps up lash volume to the max.
details: DetailsBenefitsClinique's most volumizing mascara for your loudest lash look.See 230% more volume, instantly.*Tiny dimensional fibers are deposited throughout lashes with every swipe, turning up volume to the max.The fiber-infused formula is ophthalmologist-tested, safe for sensitive eyes, and safe for contact lens wearers. Fibers may be visible on the brush.Ultra-intense pigments deliver super saturated color for high impact in one application.The innovative High-Def Wave Brush has wavy bristles to comb and coat every last lash, plus a precision tip to easily catch and define small corner lashes.Ophthalmologist-tested formula is safe for sensitive eyes and contact lens wearers.Allergy tested. 100% fragrance free.Available in Intense Black and Intense Black-Brown.Key IngredientsThe lightweight gel formula is infused with a nourishing oil blend of coconut, argan, and moringa oils to help lashes feel stronger, softer, and look healthier.Research Results230% more volume, instantly.**Clinical testing on 31 women.Also, after 1 week:96% see significant impact after 1 application.**98% say lashes look dramatically darker.**94% say lashes look healthier.**94% say lashes stay stretched and lifted all day.**95% say lashes feel comfortable all day.****Consumer testing on 166 women after using product for 1 week.Item 2612897How To UseHigh Impact High-Fi builds quickly. Starting at your lash roots, sweep the brush upward to see instant volume.Use the brush's precision tip to add definition and coat harder-to-reach corner lashes.Remove with your favorite Clinique eye makeup remover. You may see the fibers as they slip off during removal.IngredientsWater\Aqua\Eau, Acrylates/Ethylhexyl Acrylate Copolymer, Stearic Acid, Glyceryl Stearate, Synthetic Beeswax, Paraffin, Polyisobutene, Copernicia Cerifera (Carnauba) Wax\ Copernicia Cerifera Cera \Cire De Carnauba, Vp/Eicosene Copolymer, Tromethamine, Cocos Nucifera (Coconut) Oil, Argania Spinosa Kernel Oil, Moringa Oleifera Seed Oil, Ricinus Communis (Castor) Seed Oil, Caprylyl Glycol, Trimethylpentanediol/Adipic Acid/Glycerin Crosspolymer, Laureth-21, Laureth-4, PVP, Polyester-5, Hexylene Glycol, Hydroxyethylcellulose, Isostearic Acid, Aminomethyl Propanediol, Tocopheryl Acetate, Nylon-6, Silica, Disodium Edta, Phenoxyethanol. May Contain: Mica, Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491), Iron Oxides (CI 77492), Iron Oxides (CI 77499), Black 2 (CI 77266), Aluminum Powder (CI 77000), Bismuth Oxychloride (CI 77163), Bronze Powder (CI 77400), Carmine (CI 75470), Chromium Hydroxide Green (CI 77289), Chromium Oxide Greens (CI 77288), Ultramarines (CI 77007), Blue 1 Lake (CI 42090), Yellow 5 Lake (CI 19140).Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.headline: Length and Volume
reviews.comments: Love this mascara!!! Lengthen and volume...easy to take off.  Rarely flakes unless very high humidity!!

reviews.headline: Nice mascara
reviews.comments: I like that it builds quickly, it give me nice volume without applying too many layers. Fairly easy to remove also. It looks natural and doesn't get clumpy. I really like this one.

reviews.headline: Flakes off
reviews.comments: I got this mascara as a gift, part of a kit with a pink lipstick. This is probably one of the worst mascaras I've used. It flaked off my lashes in a couple of hours and collected on my lower lash line. Even after owning and using it multiple times, it still dispenses a large amount of product on the brush which makes it difficult to get an even layer on the lashes. Usually, mascaras dry out a bit and that makes it easier to apply but not this one. I would not recommend this mascara to anyone. Get the Maybelline bubble mascara or the Loreal Lash Paradise Big Deal for a much better experience and staying power at half the price.

reviews.headline: No I won't buy this product again.
reviews.comments: The woman that helped me did a great job.

reviews.headline: great mascara
reviews.comments:
This mascara is amazing! It never gets clumpy, goes on easily, and there is zero eye irritation. 
One coat adds nice volume and length that lasts all day, even in high humidity/high heat. It's also easy to remove. This will be my new go to.

reviews.headline: Formula is nice, but the bristles are coming off of the brus
reviews.comments: The formula itself and how it goes on the lashes, as well as the effect of it on the lashes is very nice. The problem is that the bristle brush is disintegrating. Every time I pull the wand out of the bottle, more of the pieces of the bristles are coming off the brush. It's defective, and unfortunately is past the "return by" date for Ulta. Otherwise I'd be returning. I've only had this mascara for maybe 6 months. The brush shouldn't be doing this.

reviews.headline: Clumpy
reviews.comments:
Not sure if old but very clumpy. I had to throw away after one use.
Definitely wish I could return.

reviews.headline: 100% recommend as an emotional girly
reviews.comments: When i tell you I SOBBED for an hour and my mascara was still perfect save for a few black specks on my cheek that were easy to remove. This mascara is so nice, rarely clumps, and does not irritate my sensitive eyes. If you like to cry but like to look gorgeous while doing it I highly recommend.

reviews.headline: Just okay.
reviews.comments: Not impressed. One swipe and its all over my lid. The lengthening is just okay, will not be repurchasing.

reviews.headline: Drying and barely visible
reviews.comments: I would not recommend this mascara. Received in a free gift package with other Clinque purchase so didn't buy. The mascara is drying and barely visible. It does not provide volume. I would not purchase as there are other products on the market that can do the job.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I've been using this mascara for about a week now, and I was pleasantly surprised by its volumizing effects! I use about 4 coats per eye and that's enough to give the illusion of wearing natural-looking falsies. Because the mascara formula is light and not thick, I've also experienced less clumping which is great as the mascaras I've been using prior would require me to constantly brush out my lashes to prevent looking like "spider eyelashes."

I have sparse, droopy, thin Asian lashes so I look for two things when buying a mascara: 1) lengthening power and 2) longevity of the product throughout the day. I would give this product 5 stars for length and 4 stars for longevity. The mascara definitely added noticeable length and volume to my lashes and is comparable to wearing thin, natural-looking falsies. If I'm going for a more dramatic, voluminous look, I would wear falsies on top, but for everyday use to mimic that effect, this mascara is perfect. I took off one star for longevity as I noticed my under eyelashes flaking off by the 5-hour mark, but I don't consider this to be a big issue considering the benefits of the product itself.

This product really changed my outlook on mascaras. I've predominantly used Asian mascaras as I figured they'd work best for my eyelashes, but Clinique challenged that mindset and I'm very happy to find a product that also works for my short, sparse Asian lashes.

I'll have to continue using it on a daily basis over a longer duration for a more thorough stance, but for now, I can confidently say that this mascara is lengthening, volumizing, and simply makes my lashes look beautiful. I would definitely recommend this product to a friend or someone I know who's on the hunt for a new mascara!
faceoff_positive.headline: Gives the illusion of wearing light, false eyelashes!

faceoff_negative.comments: I was sent this product free to test out and leave a detailed review. The mascara has more cons then pros for me personally. I'm extremely picky when it comes to mascara. My old go to for years was Maybelline Rocket mascara, until recently I switched over to a Japanese Mascara that can be purchased online or local Asian markets. In my review photo I compared the two, they both have length adding fibers. Clinique First impression, I loved the packaging/color, the wand was easy to use and a good size. As I was applying the mascara it did a decent job at separating the lashes. It did get a little clumpy as I went over it a few times which was disappointing. As I started to curl my lashes on my other eye I saw that the Clinique side completely dropped almost like the mascara weighted too much haha. My lashes had zero curl now. I do have naturally long lashes so maybe this will work better for someone with shorter lashes. I would personally not buy this mascara.
faceoff_negative.headline: Kinda Disappointed
